                "headline": "Heat Advisory issued July 19 at 8:57PM CDT until July 20 at 6:00PM CDT by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN",
                "description": "* WHAT...Heat index values of 95 to 100 expected.\n\n* WHERE...Anoka, Carver, Dakota, Hennepin, Ramsey, Scott, Washington,\nRice, and Goodhue Counties.\n\n* WHEN...From noon to 6 PM CDT Monday.\n\n* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat\nillnesses.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The highest heat indices will occur in the\nearly to mid afternoon hours before drier air moves in.",
